<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <title>CSS Grid Layout: 'vertical-align' has no effect on a grid item within an inline grid</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Manuel Rego Casasnovas" href="mailto:rego@igalia.com" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css-grid-1/#grid-containers" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#propdef-vertical-align" />
        <link rel="match" href="../reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square.xht" />
        <meta name="assert" content="This test checks that 'vertical-align' is ignored in grid items within an inline grid." />
        <style>
            #reference-overlapped-red {
                position: absolute;
                background-color: red;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                z-index: -1;
            }

            .inline-grid {
                display: inline-grid;
            }

            .inline-block-overlapping-green {
                display: inline-block;
                background-color: green;
                width: 100px;
                height: 50px;
            }

            .vertical-align {
                vertical-align: 125px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

        <div id="reference-overlapped-red"></div>

        <div class="inline-grid">
            <div class="inline-block-overlapping-green"></div>
            <div class="inline-block-overlapping-green vertical-align"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
